## FIX STRATEGY

### Fix 1: Add Optimistic Comment to UI Immediately
**File:** `CommentThread.tsx` - `handleReply()`

After successful API response, immediately add the new comment to local state:
```typescript
// After API success
const newComment = response.data;
// Add to local comments array immediately (optimistic update)
setLocalComments(prev => [...prev, newComment]);
// Also add to processingComments with the ACTUAL comment ID
onProcessingChange?.(newComment.id, true);
```

### Fix 2: Fix processingComments Tracking in handleNewComment
**File:** `RealSocialMediaFeed.tsx` - `handleNewComment()`

```typescript
// Line 806 - DON'T reload immediately
// Instead, add the new comment to local state first
setPostComments(prev => ({
  ...prev,
  [postId]: [...(prev[postId] || []), result.data]
}));

// Keep processingComments tracking the new comment ID
// Wait for WebSocket 'complete' event to clear it
```

### Fix 3: Emit 'waiting' State Immediately on Comment Creation
**File:** `api-server/server.js` - POST `/api/agent-posts/:postId/comments`

After creating comment, emit the initial state:
```javascript
// Line ~1728 - After comment creation
websocketService.emitCommentState({
  commentId: createdComment.id,
  postId: postId,
  state: 'waiting',
  timestamp: Date.now()
});
```

### Fix 4: Force Reload When Comments Section Opens
**File:** `RealSocialMediaFeed.tsx` - toggle comments handler

When opening comments section, always fetch fresh data:
```typescript
const handleToggleComments = (postId) => {
  setShowComments(prev => ({...prev, [postId]: !prev[postId]}));
  if (!showComments[postId]) {
    // Opening - force fresh fetch
    loadComments(postId, true);
  }
};
```

